UR  - https://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/pii/0304387878900329
AB  - Although the impact of demographic variables on economic development is an issue of great concern, population characteristics have not been systematically analyzed in the literature on tax ratios and economic development. This paper examines the issue of demographic effects on tax ratios using a cross-section econometric model derived from simple structural relationships, permitting inferences to be made regarding the strengths of supply versus demand influences on tax ratios.
